description: This project was built out of a need for a library to manage credentials files (similar to AWS credentials), their attributes, sessions, and environment variables.

interact_justification: This is currently included in the GitHub Repository (https://github.com/engi-fyi/go-credentials/) which is linked to on the page.

vulnerability_report_private_justificati: Reports can be emailed to security@engi.fyi privately. This process is documented at https://github.com/engi-fyi/go-credentials/security/policy.
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: Bug actioned within 72 hours. If a fix provided actioned within 24 hours as per https://github.com/engi-fyi/go-credentials/security/policy.
build_floss_tools_justification: All commands can be run manually and are mostly dependant on core golang tools.
tests_are_added_justification: As per contribution guide (https://github.com/engi-fyi/go-credentials/blob/feature/community-documents/CONTRIBUTING.md) all new features must past a quality gate on our SonarCloud instance (https://sonarcloud.io/dashboard?id=engi-fyi_go-credentials) which requires at least 80% code coverage. Our CI pipeline ensures tests must also pass.
